          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " on railroad companies to voluntarily ‚Äútake urgent, dedicated action that includes not just complying with current standards but decisively putting the long-term safety of workers and communities ahead of short-term opportunities to supercharge profits.‚Äù",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Proposed actions for the railroads to take include speeding up plans to phase-in safer tank cars for hazardous materials before they are federally required in 2029, notifying state emergency responders when trains are carrying hazardous gases through their states, and providing paid sick leave to rail workers.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Railroad union leaders were less than impressed with the department asking the railroad giants to voluntarily make these changes.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "button",
        "alignment": "center",
