        "buttonUrl": "https://dailyposter.outpost.pub/ghost-integration/60818189ad12f332071054b8/tips"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "‚ÄúPete Buttigieg ‚Äî like any other bureaucrat or politician ‚Äî is a master of pontification, [saying]: ‚ÄòI believe this. And we could do that,‚Äô‚Äùsaid Ron Kaminkow, the general secretary at Railroad Workers United. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt give a damn what you believe. And I don‚Äôt give a damn what we should do. Make it happen.‚Äù",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "‚ÄúAll of that nonsense about urging and encouraging the Class I rail carriers is simply grandstanding and ineffectual,‚Äù Kaminkow continued. ‚ÄúIt is bullshit. Make the bastards do it!‚Äù",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
